    "This approach has been utilized in (Wang et al., 2020), where the reviews are summarized in the form of a textual summary and a structured graph.",
    "Here, for explainaing the review summaries, a text instance is picked from the original text corpus to explain the generated summary.",
    "Ismail et al. (2023) use the Input Reduction (Feng and Boyd-Graber, 2019) and HotFlip Feature importance.",
    "Feature importance methods aim to explain the outcome by assigning importance scores to input features, such as lexical features including word/tokens and n-grams, clustering over NN embeddings (Schaper et al., 2022), or manual features obtained from feature engineering.",
    "Two popular operations to enable feature importance-based explanations are first-derivative saliency and attention mechanism."
